Key Match Events: Wales took the lead in the 11th minute after Harry Wilson's effort was saved and Brennan Johnson scored from close range.
Wales extended their lead in the 29th minute with Harry Wilson's powerful strike.
Iceland pulled one back in the 69th minute with Logi Tomasson's curling shot.
Iceland equalized in the 72nd minute when Danny Ward deflected the ball into his own net.
Post-Match Reflections: Wales, unbeaten under Craig Bellamy, are second in the group with five points.
Iceland are third with four points and will host Turkey next, while Wales face Montenegro.
